node.title: Biden plans first Europe visit since Ukraine invasion as refugees surpass 3m
node.description: There is confirmation the US president will meet with NATO leaders next week as the UN announces more than 3 million have now fled Russia's attacks on Ukraine.

node.title: Briscoe Group reports lift in full-year profit
node.description: Briscoe Group says it is "thrilled" with a strong lift in full-year profit amid another challenging year of Covid-19 lockdowns, supply chain disruptions and economic volatility.

node.title: Doctor who worked on COVID vaccine​ talks changing the game in science
node.description: At just 36 years old, Corbett worked night and day with a team of scientists developing Moderna's COVID-19 vaccine​ in record time.

node.title: Blues win their Super Rugby Aupiki opener
node.description: The Blues have won their first match in Super Rugby Aupiki, beating Matatu 21-10 in Hamilton.

node.title: Russian TV employee who protested war in Ukraine speaks out
node.description: Channel One editor and producer Marina Ovsyannikova interrupted Monday night's broadcast with a sign that said: "You are being lied to."

node.title: NATO plans for more troops on eastern flank after Russia's Ukraine invasion
node.description: NATO is set to tell its military commanders to draw up plans for new ways to deter Russia following Moscow's invasion of Ukraine, including more troops and missile defences in eastern Europe…

node.title: RATs in schools will up student attendance, 'bring down anxiety levels'
node.description: Schools and early childhood centres hope hundreds of thousands of rapid antigen tests (RATs) will keep attendance up and put staff and students at ease.

node.title: Tsunami advisory and power outages as big quake strikes off Japan

node.title: How would a Russian debt default affect global markets?
node.description: IMF head Kristalina Georgieva says a Russian default on its foreign debt is no longer an "improbable event."

node.title: Ukraine leader says Russia's positions in talks "sound more realistic"
node.description: Putin's relentless assault on Ukrainian cities continues to take a devastating toll, but both Moscow and Kyiv are hinting at possible progress in negotiations.

node.title: 18-year-old charged with manslaughter after 4-year-old brother shoots self

node.title: Watch Live: Biden, lawmakers respond to Zelenskyy's plea

node.title: Zelenskyy calls for no-fly zone over Ukraine in emotional plea to U.S. Congress
node.description: "Being the leader of the world means to be the leader of peace," the Ukrainian president told lawmakers in a virtual address.

node.title: Injured Fox correspondent evacuated from Ukraine after deadly attack
node.description: "Ben is alert and said to be in good spirits," Fox anchor Bill Hemmer told viewers Wednesday morning.

node.title: Omicron sub-variant BA.2 spreading across U.S. as cases rise overseas
node.description: Despite the spread of the new sub-variant, U.S. daily cases and hospitalizations continue to drop while deaths plateau.

node.title: Federal Reserve expected to raise rates

node.title: U.S. says Russian troops "killed 10 people standing in line for bread"

node.title: Starbucks' Howard Schultz to return as CEO Johnson retires

node.title: Watch Live: Zelenskyy addresses Congress amid push for more weapons
node.description: Senate Majority Leader Chuck Schumer said it's "nearly unheard of" to have a foreign head of state who is "fighting for his life" to address Congress.

node.title: Biden administration to shield Afghans in the U.S from deportation
node.description: Temporary Protected Status (TPS) will allow eligible Afghans to live and work in the U.S. without fear of deportation.

node.title: Minnesota family says Russia detained their son after Ukraine invasion

node.title: Climate change to make pollen season longer and nastier, study says
node.description: As the world warms, allergy season will last longer and pollen levels could as much as triple in some places, a new study says.

node.title: Dog-sitter recovering after losing face in horrific dog attack
node.description: It was pure luck that she was rescued alive.

node.title: Utah biologists capture, collar and release wolverine for first time
node.description: Officials with the Utah Division of Wildlife Resources said ​it was just the eighth confirmed wolverine sighting in Utah since 1979.

node.title: Fox News cameraman, local producer killed in attack that wounded correspondent
node.description: Wounded correspondent Benjamin Hall remains hospitalized, the network says.

node.title: Fake heiress Anna Sorokin fighting deportation from U.S.

node.title: Multiple dead in crash involving college men's and women's golf teams

node.title: Another journalist shot to death in Mexico, eighth so far in 2022

node.title: Rare video shows Burmese python defending nest from bobcat in Florida
